RJR Nabisco Posts
   4th-Quarter Profit
   Of $161 Million
Sales rose 7.8% to $3.98 billion from $3.69 billion.
   Food-business sales rose 9% to $1.78 billion from the
year-earlier period, when Latin American food operations
weren't consolidated in the figures.
   For RJR's tobacco business, sales rose 7% to $2.2 billion,
mostly due to gains in Europe and the Middle East. But
tobacco sales volume in the U.S. declined, the company noted.
Volume declines and increased marketing expenditures more
than offset favorable pricing, the company said.
   Total interest expense fell to $471 million from $676
million.
   For the full year, RJR posted net income of $368 million,
or 22 cents a share, compared with a loss of $429 million, or
$1.11 cents a share. Sales rose 8% to $14.99 billion from
$13.88 billion.
   In late composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange
yesterday, RJR Nabisco shares were quoted at $10.50, up 25
cents. With volume of more than 3.1 million shares, it was
the most active stock on the Big Board.